  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `./erigon --version`\r\n`erigon version 2.42.0-stable-beb97784`\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nLinux\r\nCommit hash: \r\nbeb97784d43ece5acde365a74efe8763692ebdba\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config):\r\n```\r\n    - --snapshots=true\r\n    - --authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0\r\n    - --authrpc.vhosts=*\r\n    - --private.api.addr=0.0.0.0:9090\r\n    - --sentry.api.addr=sentry:9091\r\n    - --downloader.api.addr=downloader:9093\r\n    - --txpool.disable\r\n    - --metrics\r\n    - --metrics.addr=0.0.0.0\r\n    - --metrics.port=6060\r\n    - --pprof\r\n    - --pprof.addr=0.0.0.0\r\n    - --pprof.port=6061\r\n    - --datadir=/home/erigon/.local/share/erigon\r\n    - --externalcl\r\n```\r\nConcensus Layer:\r\nPrysm  v4.0.1\r\nConcensus Layer Command (with flags/config):\r\n```\r\n    - --datadir\r\n    - /data\r\n    - --rpc-host=0.0.0.0\r\n    - --monitoring-host=0.0.0.0\r\n    - --execution-endpoint=http://erigon:8551\r\n    - --jwt-secret=/jwt.hex\r\n    - --accept-terms-of-use\r\n```\r\nChain/Network: \r\nEthereum\r\n\r\n### RPC call\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"method\": \"eth_call\",\r\n    \"params\": [\r\n        {\r\n            \"to\": \"0xA0b86991c6218b36c1d19D4a2e9Eb0cE3606eB48\",\r\n            \"data\": \"0x70a082310000000000000000000000000A59649758aa4d66E25f08Dd01271e891fe52199\"\r\n        },\r\n        \"<blocknum>\"\r\n    ],\r\n    \"id\": \"0\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n<blocknum>=`latest` gives\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"result\": \"0x000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000804e707ba3e02\",\r\n  \"id\": \"0\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n<blocknum>=`0x104b637` should give\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"error\": {\r\n     \"code\": -32000,\r\n     \"message\": \"Invalid...\"\r\n  }\r\n  \"id\": \"0\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n<blocknum>=`latest` gives\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"result\": \"0x000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000804e707ba3e02\",\r\n  \"id\": \"0\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n<blocknum>=`0x104b637` gives\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"result\": \"0x\",\r\n  \"id\": \"0\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nQuery against a block number > latest for your node\r\n",
